block content

  +state('Montana', '/assets/images/flag-montana.svg', 'The Treasure State', 'November 8, 1889')

  .intro
    p The Montana state flag was first flown by the First Territorial Infantry during the Spanish-American War. Colonel Harry C. Kessler commissioned this flag featuring the state seal on a field of blue.
    p The flag was officially adopted February 7, 1905, with the only change made to eliminate the text “1st Montana Infantry U.S.V.”
    p In 1981, the word “Montana” was added to the flag and in 1985, it was specified that Helvetica Bold be used.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Montana flag features a field of blue charged with the state seal, in full color, centered.
      p Above the seal, the word “Montana” is inscribed in gold.
    .visual.flag
      img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-montana.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-montana-icon-tools.svg')
          h4 tools
          p farming, mining
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-montana-icon-motto.svg')
          h4 motto
          p natural resources, #[em Gold and Silver]
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-montana-icon-nature.svg')
          h4 nature
          p natural beauty, the Great Falls of the Missouri River, the Rocky Mountains
        li.icon-item

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The Montana seal and coat of arms was designed in 1865 by Francis Thompson.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/coat-of-arms-montana.jpg')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Montana statute does not specify color values for the flag.
    .visual
